The **Batch Workloads **service allows to scale Doxee Platform Batch processes.

> Note

For more information on Batch processes, see [Batch Workflow Documentation](/doxee-platform/docs/batch-workflows) and [Doxee Platform Batch Jobs Documentation](/doxee-platform/docs/batch-jobs).

## Accessing the Batch Workloads service
- Access the Doxee Platform home page.

- Click ![](data:image/png;base64,) on the navigation bar to expand the menu.

- Select **Batch Workloads**.

![](data:image/png;base64,)	

The Batch Workloads service is opened in a new browser tab.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

Batch Workloads consists of three sections:

**Section**

**Description**

[**Tenant**](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-batch-workloads-user-manual#tenant-resources)

View and edit the maximum number of running jobs, production tasks, delivery tasks and assigned memory for the selected tenant

[**Workflows**](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-batch-workloads-user-manual#workflows-resources)

View and edit the maximum number of running jobs, production tasks and delivery tasks for each workflow belonging to an account associated with the selected tenant

[**Components**](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-batch-workloads-user-manual#components-resources)

View and edit the maximum number of running tasks for each Batch Workflows component

For more information on the editing options, refer to the respective sections below.

## Tenant resources
The **Tenant **section provides an overview of the maximum numbers of concurrently running jobs, production tasks, delivery tasks, and memory for the selected tenant. It is possible to scale these numbers for the selected tenant.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

The **Tenant **section includes the following fields:

**Field**

**Description**

**Jobs**

Maximum number of jobs running in parallel for the selected tenant

**Production tasks**

Maximum number of production tasks running in parallel for the selected tenant

**Delivery tasks**

Maximum number of delivery tasks running in parallel for the selected tenant

**Memory**

Memory assigned to the selected tenant (in GiB)

### Editing tenant resources
To scale the resources for the selected tenant up or down, click the  ![](data:image/png;base64,)  **Edit **icon in the top right corner of the Tenant section. A pop-up window is shown:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Field**

**Description**

**Jobs (instances)**

Enter the maximum number of jobs which shall be able to run in parallel for the selected tenant

**Production tasks (instances)**

Enter the maximum number of production tasks which shall be able to run in parallel for the selected tenant

**Delivery tasks (instances)**

Enter the maximum number of delivery tasks which shall be able to run in parallel for the selected tenant

**Memory (GiB)**

Enter the amount of memory (in GiB) allocated for the selected tenant

> Note

All fields are optional.

Scaling a resource to 0 is not allowed.

## Workflows resources
The **Workflows **section provides an overview of the workflows of all accounts associated with the selected tenant. It is possible to scale the numbers of concurrently running jobs, production tasks and delivery tasks for each workflow individually.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

The **Workflows **table includes the following columns:

**Column**

**Description**

**Account**

Name of the account associated with the selected tenant

**Workflow**

Name of the workflow belonging to the account

**Jobs**

Maximum number of jobs running in parallel for the workflow

**Production tasks**

Maximum number of production tasks running in parallel

**Delivery tasks**

Maximum number of delivery tasks running in parallel

### Searching workflows
The workflows can be filtered by status, and searched.

**Filter**

**Description**

**All**

All workflows are displayed

**Custom**

Only workflows which have at least one custom resource are displayed

Search bar

Enter a text to search the **Account **or **Workflow **columns (exact or partial match)

### Editing workflow resources
To scale the resources for an individual workflow up or down, hover over the name of the workflow and click the![](data:image/png;base64,)  **Edit **icon on the right side of the table. A pop-up window is shown:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Field**

**Description**

**Jobs**

Enter the maximum number of jobs which shall be able to run in parallel for the selected workflow

**Production tasks**

Enter the maximum number of production tasks which shall be able to run in parallel for the selected workflow

**Delivery tasks**

Enter the maximum number of delivery tasks which shall be able to run in parallel for the selected workflow

> Note

All fields are optional.

Scaling a resource to 0 is not allowed

## Components resources
The **Components **section provides an overview of the workflows of all accounts associated with the selected tenant. It is possible to scale the number of concurrently running jobs, production tasks and delivery tasks for each workflow individually.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

The **Components **table includes the following columns:

**Column**

**Description**

**Component**

Name of the Batch Workflows component (see [Batch Workflows Task Reference](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-batch-workflows-task-reference))

**Tasks**

Maximum number of tasks of this component running in parallel for the selected tenant

### Searching components
The workflows can be filtered by status, and searched.

**Filter**

**Description**

**All**

All components are displayed

**Custom**

Only components which have at least one custom resource are displayed

Search bar

Enter a text to search the **Component **column (exact or partial match)

### Editing component resources
To scale the resources for an component up or down, hover over the name of the workflow and click the ![](data:image/png;base64,)  **Edit **icon on the right side of the table. A pop-up window is shown:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Field**

**Description**

**Tasks**

Enter the maximum number of tasks of this component which shall be able to run in parallel for the selected tenant

> Note

All fields are optional.

Scaling a resource to 0 is not allowed.
